{{Infobox Museum |name = Centre d'Art Contemporain Genève |image = Centre d'Art Contemporain Genève.jpg |caption = Bâtiment du Centre d'Art Contemporain Genève à la Rue des Vieux-Grenadiers 10, Genève |imagesize = |map_type = |map_caption = |coordinates = {{coord|46.198733|6.137668|display=inline}} |established = 1974 |dissolved = |type = [[Kunsthalle]] |visitors = |director = Andrea Bellini |publictransit = |website = {{url|http://www.centre.ch}} |logo=|former_name=}}
The '''Centre d'Art Contemporain Genève''' ('''Centre''') is a [[contemporary art]] exhibition centre (a ''[[Kunsthalle]]'') in [[Geneva]], [[Switzerland]], founded by [[Adelina von Fürstenberg]] in 1974.<ref name="saatchi">[http://www.saatchi-gallery.co.uk/dealers_galleries/Gallery/Centre+d%27Art+Contemporain+Geneve/16393.html Centre D’Art Contemporain Genève], [[Saatchi Gallery]], UK.</ref>
The Centre was the first contemporary art institution in [[Suisse Romande]] (i.e. in French speaking Switzerland).<ref name="saatchi" /> As a ''Kunsthalle'', it does not have a collection, but organizes temporary exhibitions and projects with regional and international artists.
The Centre d'Art Contemporain Genève gained international renown with exhibitions by artists such as [[Joseph Beuys]], [[Martin Boyce]], [[Olaf Breuning]], [[Maurizio Cattelan]], [[Roberto Cuoghi]], [[Gilbert & George]], [[Nan Goldin]], [[Dan Graham]], [[Joan Jonas]], [[On Kawara]], [[William Kentridge]], Robert Overby, [[Pipilotti Rist]], [[Ugo Rondinone]], [[Sterling Ruby]], [[Thomas Scheibitz]], [[Shirana Shahbazi]], [[Cindy Sherman]], [[Josh Smith (artist)|Josh Smith]], [[Andy Warhol]], [[Lawrence Weiner]], [[Christopher Wool]].
In 2010, the Centre took on the mission of the [[Centre pour l’Image Contemporaine]] (CIC), established in Geneva in 1985.<ref name="cic">[http://www.centreimage.ch/cic.php The Centre for Contemporary Image] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101206121032/http://www.centreimage.ch/cic.php# |date=2010-12-06 }}, Centre pour l’Image Contemporaine, Geneva, Switzerland.</ref> CIC was established to organize events and exhibitions of images using new technologies such as video, multimedia, and the Internet, as well as more traditional photography and film ([[Biennale of Moving Images|Biennale de l'Image en Mouvement]]).
==Directors== * 1974 – 1990 [[Adelina von Fürstenberg]] * 1990 – 2001 [[Paolo Colombo]] * 2002 – 2011 [[Katya García-Antón]] * 2012 – present [[Andrea Bellini (curator)|Andrea Bellini]]
==Literature== * Andrea Bellini (ed.), ''Centre d'Art Contemporain Genève 1974-2017'',Genève 2017, {{ISBN|978-2-9701054-1-1}}.
